# init(id:donationLimit:)

**Initializer**

Creates an event.

## Declaration

```swift
init(id: String, donationLimit: Tips.DonationLimit) where DonationInfo == Tips.EmptyDonation
```

## Parameters

- **id**: Unique identifier for persisting the event and its donations.
- **donationLimit**: Maximum number and maximum age of donations this event will persist and query.

### Creating an event

Create an event when you want display a tip based on an action that can occur one or more times in your app (such as a user logging in). Then use [doc://com.apple.TipKit/documentation/TipKit/Tips/Event/donate()] to donate to the event when the action occurs, increasing the event count by one.

```swift
struct LandmarkDetailView: View {
    let landmark: Landmark

    var body: some View {
        VStack {
            Text(landmark.name)
            Text(landmark.description)
        }
        .task {
            let donationInfo = DidViewLandmark(landmarkName: landmark.name)
            await Self.didViewLandmark.donate(donationInfo)
        }
    }

    static let didViewLandmark = Event(id: "didViewLandmark")
}
```

### Adding event rules

Add tip display rules using the `#Rule` macro to prevent a tip from being displayed until an event has been donated a specific number of times.

```swift
struct FavoriteLandmarkTip: Tip {
    var rules: [Rule] {
        // Tip will only display when the didViewLandmark event has been donated 3 or more times.
        #Rule(LandmarkDetailView.didViewLandmark) {
            $0.donations.count >= 3
        }
    }
}
```

## Properties

- **donations**: Returns an events existing donations.

## Add Donations

- **donate()**: Donates an event with no associated `Donation` value.
- **donate(_:)**: Donates an event along with its associated `Donation` value.
- **sendDonation(_:)**: Asynchronously donates an event with no associated `Donation` value.
- **sendDonation(_:_:)**: Asynchronously donates an event along with its associated `Donation` value.
